# Maven and Java Coding Standards

## Maven Configuration

### Project Structure
- **Main POM**: [pom.xml](mdc:pom.xml) - Central Maven configuration
- **Java Version**: Java 21 (source and target)
- **Build Tool**: Maven 3.11.0

### Key Dependencies
- **Cucumber**: 7.4.1 for BDD testing
- **RestAssured**: 4.0.0 for API testing
- **TestNG**: 7.1.0 for test execution
- **ExtentReports**: 5.1.1 for reporting
- **Jackson**: 2.9.8 for JSON processing

### Maven Plugins
- **maven-compiler-plugin**: 3.11.0 (Java 21)
- **maven-surefire-plugin**: 2.19.1 (TestNG integration)
- **maven-cucumber-reporting**: 2.8.0 (HTML reports)

## Java Coding Standards

### Package Structure
```
com.Bizom
├── BizomWebAPI/
│   └── feature/      # BizomWebAPI feature files
├── IntegrationAPI/
│   └── feature/      # IntegrationAPI feature files
├── RetailerAPI/
│   └── feature/      # RetailerAPI feature files
├── stepDefinitions/  # Shared step implementation classes
├── runner/          # Test runners for each suite
└── hooks/           # Cucumber hooks

com.Bizom.commonUtils
├── ResourceURIS.java  # Endpoint management
├── RestAssuredUtils.java # API utilities
├── JsonUtils.java    # JSON utilities
└── ConfigReader.java # Configuration management
```

### Naming Conventions

#### Classes
- **Step Definitions**: `{Action}Steps.java` (e.g., `GetSteps.java`, `PostSteps.java`)
- **Utilities**: `{Purpose}Utils.java` (e.g., `JsonUtils.java`, `RestAssuredUtils.java`)
- **Base Classes**: `{Purpose}Base.java` (e.g., `ApiTestBase.java`)

#### Methods
- **Step Methods**: Use descriptive Given/When/Then patterns
- **Utility Methods**: Use camelCase with action verbs (e.g., `parseJson()`, `sendRequest()`)
- **Constants**: Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE

#### Variables
- Use meaningful names that describe purpose
- Follow camelCase convention
- Use final for constants

### Code Organization

#### Step Definition Classes
```java
public class GetSteps {
    // GET request implementations
    @When("I send the GET request to {string} endpoint")
    public void sendGetRequest(String endpoint) {
        // Implementation
    }
}
```

#### Utility Classes
```java
public class JsonUtils {
    // Static utility methods
    public static String parseJson(String jsonPath, String response) {
        // Implementation
    }
}
```

### Exception Handling
- Use specific exception types
- Include meaningful error messages
- Log exceptions appropriately
- Fail fast for critical errors

### Documentation
- Use JavaDoc for public methods
- Include parameter descriptions
- Document return values
- Add usage examples for complex methods

## Build Configuration

### Maven Properties
```xml
<properties>
    <maven.compiler.source>21</maven.compiler.source>
    <maven.compiler.target>21</maven.compiler.target>
    <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>
</properties>
```

### Test Execution
- Use TestNG XML configuration based on executionBase:
  - `src/test/resources/NG_XMLs/BizomWebAPI_Testng.xml` for WebApi suite
  - `src/test/resources/NG_XMLs/IntegrationAPI_Testng.xml` for Integration suite
  - `src/test/resources/NG_XMLs/RetailerAPI_Testng.xml` for Retailer suite
- Enable parallel execution where appropriate
- Configure test failure handling
- Set up proper reporting

### Dependencies Management
- Use version properties for easy updates
- Group related dependencies
- Exclude conflicting transitive dependencies
- Keep dependency versions consistent across modules